OL,3,CChildren sent to UK due to lack of
OL,4,Cfoster parents, say advocacy group
OL,6,FAn advocacy group says a lack of
OL,7,Ffoster parents in Jersey means local
OL,8,Fchildren are having to be sent to the
OL,9,FUK - something the Government disputes.
OL,11,FJersey Cares, who represent people
OL,12,Fwith care experience, say the shortage
OL,13,Fof local fostering options is a real
OL,14,Fconcern.
OL,16,FChief Executive Officer Susie
OL,17,FRichardson adds: "We had an example of
OL,18,Fa young lad who had chosen his GCSEs,
OL,19,Fwas happy at school, had friends but
OL,20,Fwithout the right home in Jersey,
OL,21,Fended up having to go to the UK.
