OL,3,CChildren sent to UK due to lack of
OL,4,Cfoster parents, say advocacy group
OL,6,FIt recently ran a campaign to recruit
OL,7,Fmore foster carers, but adds that
OL,8,Fchildren are not being sent off-island
OL,9,Fbecause of a lack of homes in Jersey.
OL,11,FInstead, it says children are sent to
OL,12,Fthe UK in instances where they may
OL,13,Fbenefit from more specialised care or
OL,14,Fa new environment further away from
OL,15,Ftheir birth parents - it can also be
OL,16,Fthe child's preference to move there.
