OL,3,CChildren sent to UK due to lack of
OL,4,Cfoster parents, say advocacy group
OL,6,FAndy Waugh, Head of Improvement,
OL,7,FFostering and Adoption, explains:
OL,8,F"Children are only placed in the UK
OL,9,Fwhen their needs are such that we
OL,10,Fhaven't got the facilities or
OL,11,Fresources on the island and they are
OL,12,Fbetter matched with people who can
OL,13,Fcare for them more appropriately in
OL,14,Fthe UK."
OL,16,FEmily Hopkins has fostered more than
OL,17,F20 children over the last six years.
